<m>The purpose of this action is to extract as much information as possible from MusicBrainz. It assumes that the folders being processed contain at most one album.
In order not to run the lookup on a folder unnecessarily, a simple heuristic is used to determine if information has already been extracted.
If the <s>MusicBrainz Import Time</s> field is present in all tracks and has the same value in all tracks, the action will not attempt the lookup of information.
If you wish to rerun the lookup, you have to delete the <s>MusicBrainz Import Time</s> User Defined Text Info items prior to calling this action.
In order for this action to run correctly, you must have enabled the <s>Preferences-MusicBrainz-General-Save Import Time</s> option. When set, the option will save the import time to a track whenever something is imported.
This next sequence will determine if there is a consistent, non empty 'MusicBrainz Import Time' for every track.
We have a consistent non empty value in 'MusicBrainz Import Time'.....get out!
Create the AcoustID fingerprints if they do not already exist.
Extract data from AcoustID if it has not already been done.

This statement will attempt to extract sufficient data to be able to access the MusicBrainz release for this album.
The release and recording ids will be imported.
The Album, Artist or Title fields are also being imported which will be identical to the information available in MusicBrainz.
The Ignore Tracks without AcoustID data option lets the function continue if for any reason any of the tracks are missing the AcoustID data which we attempted to import in the last statement. If it is missing, it is more than likely due to a fingerprint which could not be created or a 'non match' situation for the fingerprint.
The Feeling Lucky option which sets a matched release id into any ignored tracks has been set. Unless all tracks contain a release id, the following Access MusicBrainz statement will not execute.
As the Feeling Lucky allow matching to a single track option is not set, at least two tracks must have a consistent release.

The following statement will execute based on the success or failure of the preceding steps.
Loose matching is set in case not all tracks could be matched. If recording ids are available for every track, the 'loose' condition will automatically be removed.
The Custom settings table, enables the import of all available MusicBrainz data with the exception of the MusicBrainz Import Settings information. There is not point in retaining the Import Settings unless you want to run through the MusicBrainz Wizard interactively as a later date and automatically select all settings for import.

Remove all private information.
NOTE: This action will not remove all private information in m4v files.
This action does an auto search for artwork displaying the found artwork in the Artwork Viewer. The action can process multiple loaded albums.
At least one selected file has unsaved changes. You must save or revert all changes before running this action.

<m>Selecting <s>Keep</s> will retain the downloaded artwork and remove all previous artwork.
Selecting <s>Keep All</s> will retain the downloaded artwork and any previous artwork.
Selecting <s>Discard</s> will remove the downloaded artwork.
Downloaded artwork is displayed in the Artwork Viewer.

NOTE THAT THIS ACTION WILL NOT REMOVE ALL PRIVATE INFORMATION IN M4V FILES.

Auto Search for artwork then choose to keep it or not.
Warning: Do not use this action if you want to retain more than one artwork item per file.
